    <p id="p_eml_bgk_54b">Regardless of the <ph
        product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"><xref
          keyref="glossentry_perspective"><term>perspective</term></xref> or </ph>editing mode that
      you are working with, the default layout consists of the following areas:<dl
        id="dl_fml_bgk_54b">
        <dlentry id="dlentry_gml_bgk_54b">
          <dt><b>Menus</b></dt>
          <dd>Menu-driven access to all the features and functions available in <ph keyref="product"
            />. Most of the menus are common for all types of documents, but <ph keyref="product"/>
            also includes some context-sensitive and <term>framework</term>-specific menus and
            actions that are only available for a specific context or type of document.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_hml_bgk_54b">
          <dt><b>Toolbars</b></dt>
          <dd>Easy access to common and frequently used functions. Each icon is a button that acts
            as a shortcut to a related function. Some of the toolbars are common for all
              <term>perspectives</term>, editing modes, and types of documents, while others are
            specific to the particular <term>perspective</term> or mode. Some toolbars are also
              <term>framework</term>-specific, depending on the type of document that is being
            edited. <ph product="author developer editor json">All the <xref
                href="configure-toolbars.dita#configure-toolbars">toolbars can be configured</xref>
              to suit your specific needs.</ph></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_iml_bgk_54b">
          <dt><b>Helper Views</b></dt>
          <dd><ph keyref="product"/> includes a large variety of <xref keyref="glossentry_dockable"
                ><term>dockable</term></xref> views to assist you with editing, viewing, searching,
            validating, transforming, and organizing your documents. Many of the views also contain
            useful contextual menu actions, toolbar buttons, or menus. The most commonly used views
            for each <term>perspective</term> and editing mode are displayed by default and you can
            choose to display others to suit your specific needs. <ph
              product="author developer editor json">The <xref
                href="dockable-views-and-editors.dita#dockable-views-and-editors">layout of the
                views can also be configured</xref> according to your preferences.</ph></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_jml_bgk_54b">
          <dt><b>Editor Pane</b></dt>
          <dd>The main editing area in the center of the application. Each editing mode provides a
            main editor pane where you spend most of your time reading, editing, applying markup,
            and validating your documents. The editor pane in each editing mode also includes
            various contextual menu actions and other features to help streamline your editing
            tasks. Each file that has been opened has a tab at the top of the editing pane<ph
              product="author developer editor json"> and there are <xref
                href="switch-editor-tab.dita#switch-editor-tab">several ways to switch between tabs
                or move them</xref></ph>.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_kml_bgk_54b"
          product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <dt><b>Perspectives</b></dt>
          <dd><ph keyref="product"/> includes <xref
              href="editing-perspectives.dita#editing-perspectives">several different
                <term>perspectives</term></xref> that you can use to work with your documents. The
              <uicontrol product="author developer editor">Editor</uicontrol><uicontrol
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Oxygen XML</uicontrol>
            <term>perspective</term> is the most commonly used <term>perspective</term> used for
            displaying and editing the content of your XML documents, and it is the default
              <term>perspective</term> when you start <ph keyref="product"/> for the first time. <ph
              keyref="product"/> also includes a <uicontrol>Database</uicontrol>
            <term>perspective</term> that allows you to manage databases<ph
              product="developer editor developerEclipse editorEclipse"> and their connections and a
              few debugging <term>perspectives</term> that allow you to detect problems in XSLT or
              XQuery transformations</ph>.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry product="author developer editor json" id="dlentry_lml_bgk_54b">
          <dt><b>Status Bar</b></dt>
          <dd>The status bar at the bottom of the application contains some useful information when
            you are working with documents. It includes the following information, in the order it
            is displayed from left to right:<ul id="ul_mml_bgk_54b">
              <li id="li_nml_bgk_54b">The path of the current document.</li>
              <li id="li_oml_bgk_54b">The <xref
                  href="working-with-unicode.dita#working-with-unicode"><term>Unicode</term>
                  value</xref> for the character directly to the right of the current cursor
                position.</li>
              <li id="li_pml_bgk_54b">The status of the current document. The status of
                  <uicontrol>Modified</uicontrol> is displayed for documents that have not yet been
                saved. Otherwise, this section is left blank.</li>
              <li id="li_qml_bgk_54b">In <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> editing mode, the current line
                and character position is displayed.</li>
              <li id="li_rml_bgk_54b">If the <xref keyref="options_global/check-for-notifications"
                    ><uicontrol>Check for notifications</uicontrol> option</xref> is selected, this
                section will show you when new messages have been received. The types of messages
                include the addition of new videos on the <ph keyref="product"/> website, the
                announcement of upcoming webinars and conferences where the <ph keyref="product"/>
                team will participate, and more.</li>
              <li id="li_sml_bgk_54b">The memory consumption, including the memory used by the
                application and the maximum amount that is allocated to the application.</li>
              <li id="li_tml_bgk_54b">If the <xref keyref="options_global/show-memory-status"
                    ><uicontrol>Show memory status</uicontrol> option</xref> is selected, a
                    <uicontrol><image href="../img/TrashIcon16.gif"/>Free unused memory</uicontrol>
                icon is displayed in the bottom-right corner and you can use this icon to free up
                unused memory.</li>
            </ul></dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
